      "title": "Sri Lanka shares edge up in mid-day trade",
      "author": "",
      "body_lines": [
        "ECONOMYNEXT \u2013 Sri Lanka stocks gained in the first hour of trade on Friday (08).",
        "The main All Share Price Index gained 0.78 per cent or 55.10 points to 7,112.96 at 1130 hours.",
        "The most liquid index S&P SL20 gained 0.96 percent or 21.44 points to 2,250.43.",
        "Top gainers were DFCC Bank, Expolanka Holdings and LOLC Holdings. (Colombo/July8/2022)"
      ],
